  "prompt": "Is it true that NASA rejected the Big Bang theory and accepted the vedic explanation ?",
  "response": "No, that is not true. NASA has not rejected the Big Bang theory in favor of any Vedic explanation. The Big Bang theory is the prevailing cosmological model that describes the early development of the universe and is supported by a wide range of observational evidence, including the cosmic microwave background radiation and the abundance of light elements.\n\nWhile Vedic texts and philosophies offer various perspectives on the nature of the universe, they are not considered scientific theories that can be tested and validated through empirical observation in the same manner as the Big Bang theory. NASA and the broader scientific community rely on the scientific method, which involves forming hypotheses, conducting experiments, and observing the natural world to draw conclusions.\n\nIn summary, the Big Bang theory remains the dominant scientific explanation for the origins of the universe, and there has been no official endorsement of Vedic cosmology in this context.",
